+{"id":"bd-1im0b","title":"[Dashboards] Persist sharing viewers/editors","description":"## Issue\\nDashboard create/update accepts sharing.viewers/editors, but the service drops them and returns empty arrays. Permissions are never persisted to dashboard_permissions, so shared access is lost.\\n\\n## Evidence\\n- apps/gateway/src/services/dashboard.service.ts:66-90 (rowToDashboard sets viewers/editors empty)\\n- apps/gateway/src/services/dashboard.service.ts:165-175 (createDashboard comment: viewers/editors from input are lost)\\n- apps/gateway/src/services/dashboard.service.ts:330-410 (listDashboards uses permissions table for access but create/update never write to it)\\n\\n## Impact\\nSharing settings are ignored; users cannot grant view/edit access via API because permissions are not written.\\n\\n## Recommended Fix\\n- On create/update, write viewers/editors to dashboard_permissions (upsert).\\n- On get/list, populate sharing.viewers/editors from permissions.\\n- Add tests to cover create/update with sharing lists.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-30T18:36:06.234071280Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-30T18:36:21.347711100Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
